      <h2>Different people.<br>Same open ear.</h2>
      <p>SafeBuds fits four kinds of Indian buyers. Pick yours.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sb-tab-bar r">
      <button class="sb-tab active" onclick="sbTab(this,'sb-p-wfh')">💼 WFH Pro</button>
      <button class="sb-tab" onclick="sbTab(this,'sb-p-bridge')">🌍 Multilingual</button>
      <button class="sb-tab" onclick="sbTab(this,'sb-p-entertain')">🎧 Entertainment</button>
      <button class="sb-tab" onclick="sbTab(this,'sb-p-parent')">👨‍👩‍👧 Parent</button>
    </div>

    <!-- WFH Pro -->
    <div id="sb-p-wfh" class="sb-panel active">
      <div class="sb-panel-img">
        {% if section.settings.panel_wfh_image != blank %}
          <img src="{{ section.settings.panel_wfh_image | image_url: width: 700 }}" width="700" height="525" alt="WFH professional with SafeBuds" loading="lazy"/>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      <div class="r">
        <span class="panel-eyebrow">The WFH Professional</span>
        <h3>6th meeting. Ears still fine. Notes already written.</h3>
        <p class="sb-panel-scene">4:30pm. Gurgaon home office. You've been on calls since 10. Chai is cold. Another Teams invite just landed. Your ears don't hurt yet — that used to not be true.</p>
        <p class="sb-panel-body">SafeBuds sit outside your ear canal, so six hours of back-to-back calls don't leave you with that pressure-and-heat buildup you've accepted as normal. And SphereLingo™ takes your meeting notes in real-time — so you stop choosing between speaking and writing.</p>
        <div class="sb-panel-pts">
          <div class="sb-pt"><div class="sb-pt-dot"></div><span>Open ear — no pain at 5pm, no infections from all-day use</span></div>
          <div class="sb-pt"><div class="sb-pt-dot"></div><span>Quad ENC mic — colleagues hear you, not your kitchen sounds</span></div>
          <div class="sb-pt"><div class="sb-pt-dot"></div><span>Auto meeting notes — transcribed and summarised after every call</span></div>
          <div class="sb-pt"><div class="sb-pt-dot"></div><span>35 hours total battery — charge Sunday, wear all week</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Multilingual -->
